nfrequencies. Thus, while in the single-phase flow the thermal boundary layers\ncontrol the heat transport, once the bubbles are injected, the bubble-induced\nliquid agitation governs the process from a very small bubble concentration\nonwards.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Feb 2018 16:26:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-09"}
